  "body": "Scenario:\r\n1. A node is already synced via FastSync (not by SnapSync) and is processing.\r\n2. The node is stopped and the binaries are updated to the latest version including Snap Sync. The config is set to SnapSync = true\r\n3. The node is started\r\n4. The Node should start SnapSync but continue processing\r\n\r\nWe need to figure out if a node already has downloaded full state at some point in the time and how far this state is behind the HEAD.\r\nSo a few things to investigate - starting from MultiSyncModeSelector. We have there a variable called best. It contains a snapshot of the blockchain state in the node - what we have downloaded so far. It contains for example State property.\r\n",
